cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.GT, cs.CG, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques to insert synthetic objects into existing photographs. 
2. cs.GR (Graphics) is also a likely category as the paper involves rendering synthetic objects with different materials and accounting for lighting interactions between the objects and the scene. 
3. cs.GT (Computer Graphics) is another possible category as the paper deals with creating physical models of the scene for rendering synthetic objects. 
4. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a possible category as the paper involves geometric modeling of the scene and objects for rendering. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper has applications in the movie and gaming industry, as well as user content creation.
